                           <locus target="#115v">Fol. 115v</locus>: Ownership note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 115v: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቀር[ነ]፡ ሰበር፡ ዘተሣየጣ፡ በወርቁ፡ ወልደ፡ ድንግል፡ [ወብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሕይወት፡ ወቀይሰ፡ ገበዝ፡ አቡነ፡] ድምጸ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወጳጳስነ፡ አቡነ፡ [ሰላ]ማ፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዝ፡ {ይኩን}፡ በአፈ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ [n.l.] አሜን።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 115v: This is a book of the church of St. Michael of Qär[nä]säbär which was bought by Wäldä Dǝngǝl with his own money [and his wife Wälättä Ḥǝywät, and qäyǝsä gäbäz …] Dǝmḍä Mikaʾe[l and by our bi]shop ʾabunä [Säla]ma. He who steals [this book] or erases [its text] {shall be} excommunicated by the word of Peter … Amen.</q>
                           Written in red ink, partly unreadable; the note mentions the donors and ʾabunä Sälama (in tenure 1841-67).
                        </item>
